{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/scaling-real-estate-portfolio.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-gantt"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>Building a Real Estate Portfolio <span>Scaling Up</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    You've bought your first property – what's next? Discover how to set goals, manage multiple properties, and scale without burning out.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 4: Skill Building · 10 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">📈 From One Door to Many</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Scaling a real estate portfolio isn't just about buying more properties – it's about building systems, managing risk, and leveraging your capital efficiently.
                <strong>This guide covers the strategies and mindset you need to grow sustainably.</strong>
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Principles Grid -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i> Set Clear Goals</h4>
                <p>Define your target number of doors, monthly cash flow, or net worth. Goals guide your acquisition strategy and keep you focused.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-people-group"></i> Build a Team</h4>
                <p>As you scale, you can't do it alone. Cultivate relationships with lenders, contractors, property managers, and real estate agents.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Leverage & Capital</h4>
                <p>Use equity from existing properties to fund down payments on new ones. Consider HELOCs, cash‑out refis, or private money.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-shield"></i> Risk Management</h4>
                <p>Diversify by market, property type, and tenant profile. Maintain reserves and avoid over‑leverage.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deeper Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-diagram-project"></i> The Scaling Ladder</h3>
            <p><strong>Stage 1:</strong> Single‑family rentals or small multifamily (duplex–fourplex).<br>
                <strong>Stage 2:</strong> Add more units via BRRRR or savings. Start using portfolio lenders.<br>
                <strong>Stage 3:</strong> Move into larger multifamily (5+ units) or commercial. Consider syndications.<br>
                <strong>Stage 4:</strong> Diversify into different markets or asset classes (self‑storage, mobile homes, etc.).</p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Many investors get stuck because they treat each property as a one‑off. Create systems for tenant screening, maintenance requests, and bookkeeping that work across your portfolio.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: Portfolio Growth Simulator (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="portfolio-simulator">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-simple"></i> Interactive: Portfolio Growth Simulator</h3>
            <p>See how your portfolio can grow over time based on your savings, returns, and reinvestment strategy.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Starting Capital ($) <span id="startCapitalVal">50000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="startCapital" min="10000" max="500000" value="50000" step="5000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Annual Savings ($) <span id="annualSavingsVal">20000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="annualSavings" min="0" max="100000" value="20000" step="1000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Down Payment per Property (%) <span id="downPercentValScale">20</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="downPercentScale" min="5" max="40" value="20" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Average Property Price ($) <span id="avgPriceVal">200000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="avgPrice" min="50000" max="500000" value="200000" step="5000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Cash‑on‑Cash Return (%) <span id="cocVal">8</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="cocReturn" min="0" max="20" value="8" step="0.5" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Appreciation Rate (%) <span id="apprecValScale">3</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="apprecRate" min="0" max="10" value="3" step="0.5" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Years to Simulate <span id="yearsValScale">10</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="yearsScale" min="1" max="30" value="10" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="simulatePortfolio" class="btn-outline">Simulate Growth</button>
            </div>

            <div id="portfolioResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This simulator assumes you reinvest all cash flow and appreciation gains to acquire new properties. It's a simplified model – actual results depend on market conditions, financing availability, and your execution.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'scaling-real-estate-portfolio', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: Scaling a Portfolio</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. Why is building a team important when scaling?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It's cheaper than doing it yourself</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">You can't manage everything alone as you acquire more properties</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Lenders require a team</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It reduces your tax liability</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. A HELOC (Home Equity Line of Credit) can be used to:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Pay off your primary residence</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Access equity from one property to fund another's down payment</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Reduce your interest rate</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Eliminate private mortgage insurance</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. Which of the following is a common pitfall when scaling?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Having too much cash in the bank</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Over‑leveraging and inadequate reserves</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Hiring a property manager</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Diversifying across markets</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. The BRRRR method can help scale because:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It eliminates all risk</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">It recycles your capital for the next deal</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It guarantees appreciation</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It requires no down payment</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. A good rule of thumb for cash reserves when scaling is:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Several months of expenses per property</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Exactly $10,000 total</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">No reserves if you have insurance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Only what's left after buying properties</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 4 (final phase) -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 You've Completed Phase 4!</h2>
            <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">Explore the other phases or revisit any article.</p>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'real-estate-basics' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-school"></i>
                    <h3>Phase 1: Foundation First</h3>
                    <p>Start from the beginning.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'real-estate-market-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                    <h3>Phase 2: Risk Management</h3>
                    <p>Protect your investments.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'saving-for-down-payment' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-piggy-bank"></i>
                    <h3>Phase 3: Practical Execution</h3>
                    <p>Take action.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
